{
  "text": "In the experiments described here we used a fixed number of genes, namely nine, as this had proven more than enough for coping with a simple single task [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . After parsing the genome into genes, the last four coding digits of every gene determine its output behavior, a number of bits for the protein type produced and the last bit for the gene's activation type, which can be \"default on\" -active unless repressed or \"default off\" -silent until activated by regulatory sites, see fig. 2 .",
